  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has finalised its guidelines on product oversight and governance to address greenwashing risks in ESG retail banking products, providing clarity for EU financial institutions. In a significant development, the EU's MiCA transition period has ended, requiring unlicensed crypto firms to exit or face enforcement, with the European Securities and Markets Authority expanding its registry of licensed crypto firms to 280. The ESMA has also proposed annual net cost savings of up to EUR 1 billion through simplification of financial transaction reporting. Meanwhile, Standard Chartered has secured an EU MiCA license, while Paytm Europe has obtained a payment institution license from the Luxembourg regulator, highlighting ongoing regulatory activity in the EU payments and fintech space.",
